---
---
<section id="experience" class="py-24 px-6 bg-[var(--color-bg)]">
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
    <span class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-[var(--color-accent)] mb-3 block reveal">Experience</span>
    <h2 class="font-display text-[clamp(2rem,4vw,3rem)] font-normal mb-4 heading-wipe">Where I've Designed</h2>
    <p class="text-lg text-[var(--color-text-secondary)] max-w-2xl mb-12 reveal">
      Each role includes the real story behind the bullet points — including what went wrong and what I learned.
    </p>

    <!-- Role 1 -->
    <div class="bg-[var(--color-bg-card)] border border-[var(--color-border)] rounded-2xl p-7 mb-6 card-hover reveal">
      <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-start md:justify-between mb-5">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">Mortgage Fintech Company</h3>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-accent)] font-medium text-sm">Senior Product Designer → Design Lead</p>
        </div>
        <span class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] mt-1 md:mt-0">2021 – Present</span>
      </div>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-[var(--color-text-secondary)] text-[0.95rem] mb-5 list-none">
        <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-[var(--color-accent)] mt-1">•</span>Leading design for mortgage origination platform serving 50K+ monthly applicants</li>
        <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-[var(--color-accent)] mt-1">•</span>Pioneered agent-first design principles for pre-approval and rate comparison flows</li>
        <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-[var(--color-accent)] mt-1">•</span>Reduced application drop-off by 34% through rapid prototyping and user testing</li>
        <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-[var(--color-accent)] mt-1">•</span>Built and mentor team of 4 product designers</li>
      </ul>

      <button onclick="toggleContext(this)" class="text-sm font-medium text-[var(--color-accent)] hover:underline cursor-pointer mb-3 bg-transparent border-none">
        The real story →
      </button>
      <div class="ai-context">
        <div class="bg-[var(--color-accent-light)] border-l-3 border-[var(--color-accent)] rounded-r-xl p-5 mt-2">
          <p class="text-[0.95rem] text-[var(--color-text-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
            <strong class="text-[var(--color-text)]">The real story:</strong> I joined when design was an afterthought. Products like TaaS (Title as a Service) and our Data Validation platform had shipped without meaningful design input — and it showed. These failures taught me the most important lesson of my career: <strong class="text-[var(--color-text)]">the fastest path to a great product isn't skipping design — it's frontloading it.</strong>
          </p>
          <p class="text-[0.95rem] text-[var(--color-text-secondary)] leading-relaxed mt-3">
            I've since transformed how we work: prototypes reach real users within 48 hours, and design is now at the table from Day 1.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Case study callout -->
      <div class="bg-[var(--color-bg-warm)] rounded-xl p-5 mt-5 border border-[var(--color-border)]">
        <span class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-[var(--color-accent)]">Case Study</span>
        <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold mt-1 mb-1">Redesigning Pre-Approval for Humans & Agents</h4>
        <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-secondary)]">How I reduced pre-approval time from 20 minutes to 4 minutes while making the flow navigable by AI agents.</p>
        <span class="inline-block mt-3 text-sm font-medium text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">Coming Soon</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Role 2 -->
    <div class="bg-[var(--color-bg-card)] border border-[var(--color-border)] rounded-2xl p-7 card-hover reveal">
      <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-start md:justify-between mb-5">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">Fintech Startup</h3>
          <p class="text-[var(--color-accent)] font-medium text-sm">Product Designer</p>
        </div>
        <span class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] mt-1 md:mt-0">2018 – 2021</span>
      </div>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-[var(--color-text-secondary)] text-[0.95rem] mb-5 list-none">
        <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-[var(--color-accent)] mt-1">•</span>First design hire; built design system from scratch serving 3 product lines</li>
        <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-[var(--color-accent)] mt-1">•</span>Designed onboarding flow that increased activation by 52%</li>
        <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-[var(--color-accent)] mt-1">•</span>Shipped 12 major features in 18 months with 2-week sprint cycles</li>
      </ul>

      <button onclick="toggleContext(this)" class="text-sm font-medium text-[var(--color-accent)] hover:underline cursor-pointer mb-3 bg-transparent border-none">
        The real story →
      </button>
      <div class="ai-context">
        <div class="bg-[var(--color-accent-light)] border-l-3 border-[var(--color-accent)] rounded-r-xl p-5 mt-2">
          <p class="text-[0.95rem] text-[var(--color-text-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
            <strong class="text-[var(--color-text)]">The real story:</strong> This is where I learned to move fast. No research team, no design system, just me and a lot of ambiguity. I made plenty of mistakes — shipped features nobody used, over-polished things that didn't matter. But I also learned that speed creates learning. The more I shipped, the better my judgment became.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
